==Classical Nahuatl==
{{was fwotd|nci|2016|June|11}}
===Alternative forms===
* {{l|nci|xochinquauitl}} {{qualifier|obsolete spelling}}
===Etymology===
From {{compound|nci|*xōchin|cuahuitl|t1=full of or adorned with flowers|t2=tree}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|nci|[ʃoː.t͡ʃiŋˈkʷá.wit͡ɬ]}}
===Noun===
{{nci-noun|i|xōchincuahuitl|pl=xōchincuahuitl}}
# {{gloss|it is}} a blossoming [[tree]] or [[shrub]]; a tree ripe with [[flower]]s
#* '''1558-1585''', [[w:Bernardino de Sahagún|Bernardino de Sahagún]], ''Primeros memoriales'', f. 279v.
#*: Ma ya auiallo '''xochinquauitl''' itlani / nepapan quecholli ma ya in quecholli
#*:: May the many-colored birds rejoice under '''the blossoming trees'''.
